description:
Jesus has just arrived at the house of Jairus, where everyone was crying and wailing loudly, mourning his daughter. Jesus spoke with power of His word. When He speaks, the dead wake up. Death cannot be in the house when Jesus is present. He turns sorrow into joy. What’s your sorrow? Like Jesus said to Jairus, “Don’t be afraid; only believe.”
